5. ğŸ“Œ Sticky Bit
ğŸ”‘ Purpose:
Restrict who can delete files in a shared directory.

Only the file owner or root can delete their files.

ğŸ›  Examples:
bash
Copy
Edit
mkdir sticky_dir
chmod +t sticky_dir          # Quick method
chmod 1777 sticky_dir        # Full method
1 (Sticky bit) as the first digit.

ğŸ” View:
bash
Copy
Edit
